!TITLE
"LIES ARE GLUE THAT HOLDS SOCIETY TOGETHER"
!WORDS
Mike Royko, syndicated columnist from Chicago, did an article 1/18/96 
on "Lies Are Glue That Holds Society Together." In it he said: If 
they (politicians) didn't lie, most would never be elected because 
they would have to declare their candidacies by saying (something 
like):

      	'I seek this office because I have an
      	enormous ego, I love power and wheeling and
      	dealing; crave admiration, recognition, and
      	approval; am infintely more intelligent than
      	the rest of you; have an insatiable need to
      	impose my will on others; and I'm bored
      	stiff with my current station in life.
      	Incidentally, I think I can do some good if
      	   elected.'

		There’s no way that kind of honesty would work in our political 
environment. But politicians are not the only ones who will lie to 
win.
