!TITLE
THE SOUND OF FALLING CHAINS - REVIEW
!WORDS
              The Sound of Falling Chains will be used gratefully by
              many a pastor teaching Galatians and preaching from
              it. The authors have canvassed an important body of
              scholarly work on the letter and give a judicious report
              of their findings. By an engaging imaginary conversation
              among laymen, they have highlighted the central issues
              of the letter in a contemporary setting. Almost half
              the book is devoted to suggestive horniletical and
              devotional notes on key passages and texts. The whole
              displays a balanced concern for scholarship, for
              theology and for the spiritual growth of church members.
              It is pleasant to read, fruitful to reflect upon and 
remarkably 
              painless to buy.
         
