!TITLE
BABIES SAVED FROM QUAKE -- UNCLAIMED AND UNIDENTIFIED
!WORDS
From The Wall Street Journal 3/10/23

BABIES SAVED FROM QUAKES’ RUBBLE WAIT TO BE CLAIMED AND UNIDENTIFIED

We all know that over 51,000 were killed and thousands more seriously 
injured in the earthquake in Turkey and Syria. But there are 2,000 
babies there now who were saved—some after several days under rubbish 
and collapsed buildings—but who lost their parents and family .They 
are unclaimed and unidentified. Think of that. Nobody is coming for 
them and they don’t know who they are if no one comes to ask for 
them. Many of them are constantly asking where their “mama” is. That 
would kill me.
The professionals who are handling their cases are near exhaustion 
physically and psychologically themselves. 

Where do you put 2,000 babies, change their diapers, feed them at 
appropriate times? Who feeds them and what do you feed them? You 
certainly don’t feed them all the same. I’m not sure I could take it 
as much as I hurt for them. Remember: they didn’t have these babies a 
month ago.
