!WORDS
I can watch you speaking live in video . . . . which means, first, 
seeing your non-aging face (you look like you did years ago, no 
joking!), and second, hear you speak audibly.

But then, as an extra cool bonus, I can read the text of your sermon 
as you speak, several lines on screen at a time, all the while 
keeping your video present above the scrolling text.

This means . . .

I see you during the entire video presentation.
I hear you speak during the entire sermon.
And, I can read every word, several lines on my screen at a time, 
that you speak as scrolling text.

We learn from you . . . 

Visually, through your facial and body expression.
Audibly, by hearing and interpreting your words.
And, by reading the words as you speak, which enhances understanding 
in my humble, now rustic, and not worth a whole lot, educational 
opinion!

And there’s one more interesting dynamic that occurs. I have sleep 
apnea and get little good sleep. I often fall asleep and spill my 
food all over myself and the couch while watching Tv,  But I haven’t 
once fallen asleep while watching and listening to your video sermons!

The point! You should have been preaching sermons like this over your 
earlier 100+ years or so preaching span. ‘Cause your video sermons 
are clear, articulate, and interesting. They properly address the 
hearer’s reasonable attention span. They make the point and aren’t 
weighed down by all that flowery, unnecessary language that you often 
accused me of every time I opened my mouth to speak! Ha!

