!TITLE
THE CROSS IN THE MARKETPLACE
!WORDS
George McLeod, the noted  Scottish clergyman,  reminds us of how we 
need to proclaim him to our world today. He called it “The Cross in 
the Market Place.”

		                                          The Cross In The Market 
Place
                   
       I simply argue that the Cross be raised again at the center of 
the market place as well as on the steeple of the church. I am 
recovering the claim that Jesus was not crucified in a cathedral 
between two candles, but on a cross between two thieves; on the town 
garbage heap; at a crossroads so cosmopolitan that they had to write 
his title in three different languages--at the place where cynics 
talk smut and thieves curse, and soldiers gamble. Because that is 
where Christ died and that is what he died about. And that is where 
Christians should be and what Christians should be about.
!TOPICS
THE CROSS IN THE MARKET PLACE
CRUCIFIXION OF JESUS
GEORGE MCLEOD
