!TITLE
MALE INFANT MORTALITY IS HIGHER THAN FEMALE
!WORDS
Infant mortality is higher in boys than girls in most parts of the 
world. This has been explained by sex differences in genetic and 
biological makeup, with boys being biologically weaker and more 
susceptible to diseases and premature death.

The work, published in the journal Proceedings of the National 
Academy of Sciences, shows that although male babies are more likely 
to die in the last months of pregnancy, female babies have higher 
mortality overall.
!TOPICS
INFANT MORTALITY
