University Press, 2010), 8. Elsewhere, Augustine argues that it is 
right and proper to intercede for even the guilty who are condemned 
to death. Augustine, “Letter 153: Augustine to Macedonius,” in 
Letters 100–155, trans. Roland Teske, ed. Boniface Ramsey, in The 
