!TITLE
ONLY ONCE, AND NEVER AGAIN
!WORDS
"In a universe of ambiguity, this kind of certainly comes only once, 
and never again, no matter how many lifetimes you live."

Robert Kincaid to Francesca in "The Bridges of Madison County," 
spoken to her as he was leaving, never to return, never to see or 
talk to her again. They experienced a love in four days that 
surmounted anything they had ever known.

Some of us have experienced that kind of love, and it cannot be 
explained or experienced a second time.
