!END


!TITLE
THE SALVATION ARMY ON HOMELESSNESS
!WORDS
The Salvation Army says:   2/6/23

   Here in Central Virginia, we provide nights of shelter to hundreds 
of people, as well as groceries from our pantry and nutritious meals 
from our feeding program to struggling families.

   When a person comes in for food or shelter, we make sure they 
understand that we are prepared to help them make the changes that 
will remedy their problems. It shouldn't be a surprise to find out 
that not everyone wants a remedy, nor even wants to change. BEING 
HOMELESS IS SOMETIMES EASIER THAN DOING THE HARD WORK REQUIRED TO 
CHANGE THEIR CIRCUMSTANCES.

   We like to help people who want to change
