------------------------------------------------------
The West Virginia Governor's mansion nearly burned down last night.  
It got all the way to the wheels before the fire department got there.

------------------------------------------------------
A Pollack went to a yard sale and saw a beautiful vase, which he 
bought.  When he got it home, he accidentally knocked it over and a 
genie came out.  The genie said, "Man, I am so glad to get out of 
that bottle!  I've been there 350 years.  In gratitude, I will grant 
you any wish you have."

The Pollack said, "Great!  I am afraid of flying and ships don't 
travel with passengers very often these days, and they're too slow 
anyway.  Would you make a road from here in America to Poland?  I 
haven't been home for so many years, and I'd like to see my folks."

The genie said, "Gosh, I don't know.  That's pretty hard to do.  Do 
you have another wish?"  The Pollack said, "Well, people are always 
making fun of us Pollacks, and I'm getting tired of it.  Could you 
make us smarter than anybody else in the world -- whites, blacks, 
Asians, anybody?"  The genie thought a minute and said, "Do you want 
that road two lane or four lane?" 

------------------------------------------------------
A West Virginia mother sent the following letter to her son away at 
college:

Dear Son,
  Just a few lines to let you know that I am still alive.  I'm 
writing this letter slowly because I know that you cannot read very 
fast.
  You won't know the house when you come home...we've moved.
  About your father...he has a lovely job.  He has 500 men under 
him.  He is cutting the grass at the cemetery.
  There was a washing machine in the new house when we moved in, but 
it isn't working too good. Last week I put fourteen shirts into it, 
pushed down the little lever, and I haven't seen the shirts since.
  Your sister Mary had a baby this morning.  I haven't found out 
whether it is a boy or girl, so I don't know whether you are an aunt 
or uncle.
  Your Uncle Dick drowned last week in a vat of whiskey at the local 
brewery.  Some of his work mates dived in to save him, but he fought 
them off bravely.  We cremated his body and it took three days to put 
out the fire.
  It rained only twice last week; first for three days, and then for 
four days.  Monday it was so windy that one of the chickens laid the 
same egg four times.
  We had a letter yesterday from the undertaker. He said if the last 
installment isn't paid on your grandmother within seven days, "up she 
comes."
         Your loving mother .
P.S.  I was going to send you $50.00 but I had already sealed the 
envelope.
 
---------------------------------------------------------------

A man traveling through West Virginia asked one of the natives if 
they had a lot of wind blowing through those mountains.  The native 
replied:
“Wind?  Nah, we don't have much in the way of wind around here unless 
you count the times it blew so hard it turned the outside faucets on.
    Once it blew so hard it blew the sunshine off the tomatoes.
    One time the wind blew so hard it took four men to hold a blanket 
in front of a keyhold.
    The state patrol pulled all the trucks off the interstate one 
night because the wind was blowing the gleam of their headlights off 
the pavement.


