!TCAID=0
!END


!TITLE
PEACE IS A RARITY IN WORLD HISTORY
!WORDS
The Society of International Law in London did some research on war 
and peace as seen throughout all recorded history. That’s about 4,000 
years, give or take a couple of hundred. One of the most important 
things they found is this: peace is rare. Only eight percent of the 
time since the beginning of recorded history has the world been 
entirely at peace. In a total of nearly 4,000 years only 286 of them 
have been without war. It’s estimated that eight thousand treaties 
have been broken in this time. The Society found that in the last 
three centuries there have been 286 wars on the continent of Europe 
alone.

Peace, this idyllic kingdom we all say we want, is more in our 
imagination than in reality. What we say and what we do are often at 
odds. We say we want peace. Every generation says the same. Every 
generation knows that war devastates families, property, people and 
nations. There is virtually nothing good that comes from war. But we 
go to war thinking that might makes right and that somehow we shall 
be spared from the devastation that we convince ourselves our enemies 
deserve.
!TOPICS
PEACE IN WORLD HISTORY
!BASE=FRS-4/9999
!SOURCE=3
!TCAID=0
!END


!TITLE
PEACE OF MIND
!WORDS
PEACCE OF MIND

Now if you're feelin' kinda low 'bout the dues you've been paying
Future's coming much too slow
And you wanna run, but somehow you just keep on stayin'
Can't decide on which way to go
Yeah, yeah, yeah
