!SOURCE=3
!TCAID=0
!END


!TITLE
BASKETBALL STAR KILLED 3YR-OLD SON, HID BODY
!WORDS
Former UR basketball star sentenced for killing son, concealing body 
in freezer

A Chesterfield County man and former University of Richmond 
basketball star on Thursday was sentenced to 20 years in prison after 
he was convicted of killing his 3-year-old son and hiding the boy's 
remains in a freezer for more than two years.

A Chesterfield jury in July found Kassceen "Kass" Weaver, 51, guilty 
on charges of homicide, concealing a dead body and child neglect in 
connection to the October 2018 death of his son, Adon Weaver. 

The exact circumstances surrounding Adon's death remain unclear, but 
prosecutors said that, at some point on the night of Oct. 23, 2018, 
the child  suffered multiple broken bones, including a fractured 
skull and humerus. 

Despite his "clear medical distress," prosecutors said Weaver did not 
take Adon to the hospital or call 911.

"Adon was a helpless child," said Chesterfield Assistant 
Commonwealth's Attorney Joshua Loren, "and (Weaver) refused to do 
anything."

By the time Adon's mother, Dina Weaver, returned to the home that 
evening, the boy was already dead, Loren said.

Samuel B. Parker, Richmond Times Dispatch
