AVOID DISAPPOINTMENT BY HAVING NO EXPECTATIONS
!WORDS
"Sometimes we avoid disappointment by having no expectations, giving 
up hope."

"You’re never too old to be disappointed by Christmas, which means 
you’re never too old to be disappointed by life."

Christmas is a mirror. It reflects back to us the spirit we bring to 
it.

We work so hard to get ready, we anticipate so much, and then… As my 
mother-in-law always said, “There’s nothing as over as Christmas.”


John Robert McFarland
