!TITLE
1 THESSALONIANS 4:13-18
!WORDS
1 Thessalonians 4:13-18. I wish I did not have to write this 
‘reflection’, but I have promised to not ‘skip over’ the hard 
passages.   Paul writes here his belief about “the Day of the Lord.” 
A trumpet sounds, Jesus descends with souls of saints from Paradise, 
their bodies rise (transformed ‘spiritual bodies  (1 Cor. 15:44)’ to 
be reunited, living Christians caught up (the rapture) and bodies 
transformed, all united with God.  This is believed widely to be 
established factual information about how end times will begin.  I 
believe differently, so I must explain.  

The question is whether the ‘spiritual realm of existence is real’ 
and whether we will need a body again after physical death.  I begin 
with what I believe about God. IF God is Creator, and I believe 
without question that God is, then God was fully God before anything 
material existed, so God’s nature must be pure Spirit.  We have no 
evidence that God ever had any material ‘body’ except when God came 
to us in incarnation, and that was for our need and benefit.  I am 
convinced that as human persons we are two-natured, having both 
bodies and souls, our bodies being mortal and our souls immortal.  
The common expression about death, going home to be with God, is 
widely understood to mean going to a place called Paradise, but I 
believe God is everywhere always present so there is nowhere that God 
is more present than HERE.  

And, to use a personal example, there is nowhere Marguerite could 
possibly be more at home than here with God and me.   I have even 
dared to reason that the God I believe Jesus revealed would not have 
‘designed and established’ a system of personal relationships that 
would cause physical death to separate soulmates just because one had 
physically died.  Some of my colleagues tell me I am ‘projecting’ 
when I come to these conclusions.  I agree, but Paul was also 
projecting his beliefs about an event thar has not yet occurred. I 
dare to believe that Holy Spirit is still inspiring us when we seek 
to love God with our whole mind as well as our heart.  I know this is 
very non-traditional, but it is what I believe.

Sherill Stevens

FRS: The applicationhere of Paradise in questionable.
!TOPICS
1 THESSALONIANS 4:13-19
DAY OF THE LORD
SHERRILL STEVENS
