!END


!TITLE
CHANGE IS NOT COMING, ITS HERE
!WORDS
A few years ago while completing a new family life center for a 
church I was pastoring, I prepared a CD with pictures of the building 
as it was going up to place in the cornerstone, to be opened in 50 
years. Churches do that all the time. But a couple of weeks later, 
one of our men, a computer specialist for his company, jolted me when 
he said, “Preacher, I’m sure that fifty years from now they won’t 
know what to do with an old CD and very likely won’t have anything to 
play it on even if they did.” And he was absolutely correct. I was 
wasting my time, and I had gone to a lot of trouble to do that. FRS
!TOPICS
CHANGE IS NOT COMING, IT'S HERE
FRED R. SKAGGS
