!TITLE
ORAL TRADITION WORKS ON A EARTHQUAKE STORY
!WORDS
On April 5, 2024, there was a 4.7 eathquake that struck Nw Jersey and 
much of the Eastern Seaboard, including fom Boston to Washington, 
D.C. where the Washington Monument was cracked as a result.  

A seisnograp run in Richmond, Virginia that same day showed that 
NOTHING and NO PLACe in Virginia (from Washigon D.C. south) was 
affected by the earthquake. 

Nevertheless, a number of people in Virginia, including Richmond, 
reported that they had exxperienced the earthquake and described the 
response they had.

NONE OF THIS COULD BE TRUE the seismograph showd or it would have 
been registerable on the graph. 

The story has started and no doubt will continue as "I know. I was 
there when it happenend."  That's oral tradition at work.
