!TITLE
MEMORIAL DAY STILL SPEAKS TO PEOPLE WHO WILL LISTEN
!WORDS

   	Memorial Day originated during the Civil War.  A Virginia woman 
of French descent, accompanied by others, decorated the soldiers' 
graves, both Union and Confederate on this day.  Some think she chose 
May 30 because on that date Napoleon's body was returned to France 
from the island of St. Helena.  

	Whatever the reason for choosing the day, her motive was to help us 
remember -- to remember some people whose corpses could be counted -- 
to remember some people who had mothers and fathers, some with wives 
and children who grieved that they never came home, and most of all 
to remember that these people paid a high price in our behalf.
!TOPICS
