!TITLE
MARRIED TEACHER CAUGHT UNDRESSED WITH STUDENT
!WORDS
Married substitute teacher caught undressed in car with student, 
deputies say

A substitute teacher with Omaha Public Schools is facing felony 
sexual abuse charges. Source: WOWT
By Nick Stavas and Akim Powell

Published: Apr. 13, 2024 at 8:24 PM EDT|Updated: Apr. 13, 2024 

ELKHORN, Neb. (WOWT/Gray News) - A married substitute teacher was 
arrested after allegedly being caught undressed with a student, 
according to Nebraska authorities.

Douglas County Sheriff’s deputies responded to a call regarding a 
suspicious vehicle parked on a dead-end road in a neighborhood, WOWT 
reported.

When deputies arrived, they found 45-year-old Erin Ward and a 
17-year-old boy in the backseat.

Authorities said the teen jumped in the driver’s seat and attempted 
to flee from deputies before crashing.

After crashing the car, deputies saw the teen running from the 
driver’s seat without any clothes on. However, he was found more than 
an hour later in a nearby neighborhood wearing only underwear and a 
T-shirt.

Back at the scene, Ward was putting on her clothes.

She allegedly told authorities that she was a substitute teacher at 
Burke High School and other schools, WOWT reported.

Ward allegedly admitted to having sexual relations with the teen, 
according to authorities.

Deputies determined that the vehicle belonged to Ward and her spouse.

Ward was arrested and charged with one count of felony sexual abuse 
by a school employee.


