!END


!TITLE
THE CHURCH IS ALWAYS BEHIND
!WORDS
God is too smart to work only through the church. As the great church 
historian, Albert Outler, said, “The church has never done the right 
thing until pressured to do so by  the world.”

Of course, by the time we all acknowledge that this homophobic 
division is neither smart nor Christian, there may be no churches at 
all, if present trends continue. People are getting fed up with 
Christians who can’t get along with one another.

As Saul Alinsky said, “If you want to know where the action is, look 
for the reaction.” The action was in the middle. The reaction was 
everywhere else.

John Robert McFarland
!TOPICS
