!TITLE
GOLFER IGNORES DEATH IN ACCIDENT TO GET TO GOLF TEE OFF
!WORDS

5/16/24 New York Times

Scottie Scheffler, the world No. 1 golfer, was arrested on Friday by 
police ahead of the second round of the PGA Championship while 
attempting to drive around a traffic stoppage outside Valhalla Golf 
Club in Louisville, Ky.

Traffic outside the golf course had been stopped because of a crash 
that killed a pedestrian around 5 a.m. 
ESPN’s Jeff Darlington reported Scheffler attempted to continue 
driving another 10-20 yards. When he stopped, a police officer asked 
Scheffler to exit his vehicle. Darlington reported the police officer 
opened the car door and placed the 27-year-old in handcuffs and in 
the back of a police car. Video shows Scheffler in handcuffs being 
escorted by two officers.
