!TITLE
MANY TIMES I FELT AS IF YOU WERE SPEAKING DIRECTLY TO ME
!WORDS
Dr. Skaggs,

I will certainly miss your Sunday morning messages, which have meant 
a great deal to me. There were many times I felt as if you were 
speaking directly to me. You are truly a gifted preacher, and you 
will be greatly missed.
 
After Christian’s death in 2018, returning to our church, The 
Episcopal Church of the Redeemer, was difficult. Whenever we tried, 
April would cry throughout the service. Alison and Christian grew up 
in that church, and it brought back too many memories. We visited 
different churches but couldn’t find a good fit. Your messages filled 
a void in my life during that time, but I’m happy to say that we 
returned to our church in early May, and it felt like a homecoming. 
We haven’t missed a service since.
 
I wish you health and happiness as you begin a new chapter in your 
life.
 
Thank you for everything you have done for me and my family.

Bill
